    • setup

      public void setup()
      Initializes various managers and addons used by the plugin. Checks if PlaceholderAPI is enabled and sets a boolean value accordingly. This function should be called in onEnable() or after all other initialization code in onEnable().

      Failure to call this method will result in non-functioning managers and addons.

    • getPlayerMenuUtility

      public PlayerMenuUtility getPlayerMenuUtility(UUID player)
      The getPlayerMenuUtility function is used to get the PlayerMenuUtility object of a player.

      If the player doesn't have a PlayerMenuUtility object, it will be created.

      The Menu API uses this function.

      Parameters:
      player - Get the player, whose PlayerMenuUtility object should be returned
      Returns:
      The PlayerMenuUtility object of the player

    • createPlayerMenuUtility

      public PlayerMenuUtility createPlayerMenuUtility(UUID player, boolean addToList)
      The createPlayerMenuUtility function is used to create a PlayerMenuUtility object for a player.

      If the player already has a PlayerMenuUtility object, it will be overwritten.

      The Menu API uses this function.

      Parameters:
      player - Get the player, whose PlayerMenuUtility object should be created
      addToList - Determine if the PlayerMenuUtility object should be added to the hashmap
      Returns:
      The PlayerMenuUtility object of the player
